HEADWORD: Pressiroster
<hw>Pres`si*ros"ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>presssus</ets> pressed (p. p. of <ets>premere</ets>) +
<ets>rostrum</ets> beak: cf. F. <ets>pressirostre</ets>. See 4th
<er>Press</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>One of a tribe of wading
birds (<fam>Pressirostres</fam>) including those which have a compressed
beak, as the plovers.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pressirostral</ent>⟦br⟧
